Title: Feedback Seminar
Long Description: Give us your feedback! Hosted by the Convention Director and several staff members.  1:45 Unl We want to know what you liked and didn't like about Gen Con '99. Give us ideas on  how to make 2000 even better!

Open: Under a Pale Green Sky
Long Description: By Reynolds Jones and Ruth Pinsky.  The Prince has been captured.  As his friends, it is your duty to find him.  The recent assassination of the King has left the land without a decisive leader, and barons and merchants fight for control.   Is the same person behind both the kidnapping and the King's death, or is someone taking advantage of the situation?  Three-round team elimination.  Standard RPGA experience points.

Title: The Archaeoligical Society Annual Dinner
Long Description: Living Death LARP The Archaeological Society-Annual Dinner by Claire Hoffman. The results of the Jasper-Petrie Expedition (from the Gen Con ’98 "Intrigue in Egypt” module) will be presented as well as other papers and awards. Appropriate dinner costume is preferred. A Living Death interactive for heroes of all levels. This event occurs in conjunction with the RPGA late dinner in slot 4.

Title: LARP: A Strange Detente
Long Description: A Strange Detente by Melissa Maurer. Lord Thelmaran thought that his days of excitement and danger had ended along with his adventuring career. However, after inheriting a small keep in a politically contentious area, he knows the truth: politics are more dangerous than a sharp sword. Determined to earn some peace and quiet, Lord Thelmaran has invited local dignitaries and old adventuring friends alike to his newly restored keep for a party. Well, maybe it wasn’t such a good idea to have adventurers and dignitaries at the same function, but at least no one can complain of boredom . . . This event will involve plotting and scherrr ,g among the dignitaries, a chance to explore the keep and perhaps find an entrance to underground warrens, contests among the attendees, and even some famous personalities of the Realms. The event is continuous from slot to slot, so on Friday you pick up where you left off Thursday. A different event number applies to each slot to maximize flexibility. Dinner is an additional $30.00

Long Description: The Green Knight staff invites you to join them for their first Gen Con seminar. All lovers of Arthurian myths, PENDRAGON  players, potential contributors, and interested by-standers are welcome! Peter Corless.  Green Knight Publishing founder, will be on hand to answer your auestions and regale  the assembled court.

ShadowRun Q&A
Long Description: Here's the place to ask those game breaking questions. (And hopefully get some  answers). Meet the FASA ShadowRun team and learn all about the world of  ShadowRun.

Title: Live Action Chaosium Unplugged
Long Description: That's right! we're back and hosting another off the cuff and by the seats of our pants  CHAOSIUM seminar. We'll be on hand to thrill and amaze you. We'll tell you some of  the secret stuff we're doing. Hopefully we'll answer more questions than we stir up this  year. So come and hang out with us instead of eating lunch. We'll even provide tree  water. Did your mama ever warn you about Californians and Texans? Come find out  why she should have.

Title: What's Up With FASA?
Long Description: Get the scoop on what's happening at FASA Corporations. Including exciting reports on  the new VOR: The Maelstrom and Crimson Skies games.

Title: Secrets of ShadowRun
Long Description: Hear about what's new and hot in the world of ShadowRun from the man behind the  machine Mike Mulvihill.

Title: A Tale of Chivalry and Romance
A Tale of Chivalry and Romance
2nd / 3rd / Dinner Party
Long Description: Dinner Party Run by Mind’s Eye Theatre and Game Base 7. Prince Raven, the Malkavian Prince of Barstow, California has arrived in the city and is holding a Dinner Party. All Malkavians, their friends, and relatives are invited. Raven has issued a challenge. Tell him an interesting story, and he’ll give a prize to the best one. What could you do with a pint of fourth-generation Gangrel? Bring your own character. Camarilla, Sabbat, or Indy welcome.

Title: A Night At Dottie's
Long Description: A Night at Dottie’s Home Rules by Warren Dimock. Visit a 1920’s speakeasy where bootleggers, coppers, and killers converge. This is a non-vampire LARP.

Title: A Night At Dottie's
Long Description: A Night at Dottie’s Home Rules by Warren Dimock. Visit a 1920’s speakeasy where bootleggers, coppers, and killers converge. This is a non-vampire LARP.

Title: Boat Trip
Long Description: Boat Trip Home Rules by Warren Dimock. Twelve passengers travel from Paris in late 18th century Europe. Of course, no one is fleeing France or smuggling anything or hunting traitors . . . are they? This is a non-vampire LARP.

Title: Boat Trip
Long Description: Boat Trip Home Rules by Warren Dimock. Twelve passengers travel from Paris in late 18th century Europe. Of course, no one is fleeing France or smuggling anything or hunting traitors . . . are they? This is a non-vampire LARP.

Title: Train To Vienna
Long Description: Train to Vienna Home Rules by Warren Dimock. Join the spies, salesmen, lawyers, secret police, and others as they stage a military coup in late 1940’s Europe. After all, everyone is trying to escape, aren’t they? This is a non-vampire LARP.

Title: 100 Acre Wood  Treasure Hunt
Long Description: Eight characters (Pooh, Piglet, Eeyore, Tigger, Owl, Rabbit, Big Bird, and Cookie  Monster) race through the woods to try to be the first one back to the house with seven  points. Along the way players try to stop rivals by stealing their points or using items they  rind.

Title: 100 Acre Wood  Treasure Hunt
Long Description: Eight characters (Pooh, Piglet, Eeyore, Tigger, Owl, Rabbit, Big Bird, and Cookie  Monster) race through the woods to try to be the first one back to the house with seven  points. Along the way players try to stop rivals by stealing their points or using items they  find.

Title: Between the Darkness and the Light
Long Description: See LARP Pages for full text. Sponsor: Nocturne Productions.

Title: Live-Variant: Project Ra
Long Description: Project Ra You know that Pharaoh Mobius’s latest brainchild is code-named Project Ra, but that’s all you know about it. You’re not the only one who wants more information. You’ve got to find out what this is all about, or it’s curtains Core Earth. This event uses TORG Live! rules, which combine live action with all of the traditional mechanics of table-top TORG.

Title: Planetstorm
Long Description: It was only a matter of time before the Tenskin threat once again reared its ugly, bristled  head. On the remote swamp planet Qrganis, the Infranites, sworn foes of the Tenskin,  find their small military outpost is threatened when the fascist Fantasians join forces with  their age-old enemy to even the score. Global Games Planetstorm is a skirmish scale  28mm science fiction game set in a politically charged 22nd century.

Ravenloft: Courtly Manners: A Night In Ravenloft
Long Description: Courtly Manners: A Night in Ravenloft Join TSR Designer Jason Carl for this intriguing live-action roleplaying event staged in the popular Ravenloft® ADfiD® campaign setting. No LARP experience necessary. Characters provided. AD&D/ Medieval/Renaissance costumes encouraged but not necessary.

Title: Drop Zone
Long Description: AD&D/Alternity Double Blind Two parties of adventurers—one from a high fantasy, AD&D setting and the other from a high-tech, Alternity universe—must race to uncover the secret nature of a powerful artifact. Is it a magical device left over from some legendary wizards’ war, or a powerful doomsday weapon built by a long-forgotten alien species?

Title: Tangents: My Sins Remembered
Long Description: Mindwalkers: Life Is But a Dream The Psychic Wars are over. Play a group of desperate psionic freedom fighters as they try to elude search-and-destroy squads while striking one last blow for psionic independence! This scenario showcases as-yet-unreleased rules for new psionic skills and psychic combat.

Title: Discovery!
Long Description: Discovery! Duane Maxwell, Star*Drive line editor, sends you to discover and perhaps colonize a new planet. The twist is this: the results of this adventure will become part of Star*Drive history. Help create the future of the Vergeee

Title: 2nd Edition: Alba Ker VII: In Too Deep
Battleship Cage Match
Long Description: Battleship Cage Match Don’t miss this special playtest of a new set of starship combat rules focusing on the big ships: cruisers, destroyers, carriers, and battleships! What could be more fun that vaporizing your best friends with matter torpedoes and plasma cannons?

Title: 2nd Edition: 2nd Edition: Forgotten Realms - Baldur's Gate Celebrity Game
Long Description: Baldurs Gate® Celebrity Game Welcome to Baldur’s Gate, site of the bestselling Interplay computer game. There are a lot of ways to get into trouble here: author Phil Athans and editor Julia Martin lead an adventure that introduces you to a few you won’t find in the computer game.

Title: Old-School D&D
Long Description: Old-School D&D® Go back in time 25 years and play the D&D game in its original, published form (1974). Experience fast, deadly, and rather strange roleplaying. See how far we’ve come!

Title: 2nd Edition: DUNGEON Adventures Playtest
Long Description: Dungeon® Adventures Playtest Meet Chris Perkins, editor of Dungeon Adventures, and playtest an AD&D® adventure scheduled for an upcoming issue!

Title: If I Ran TSR I Would...  (Industry)
Long Description: We're going to make this panel very focused on getting ideas and feedback from  retailers and distributors. We want them to talk to us about what they would do in our  shoes. We're not going to talk about what we're doing; this is going to be a session  where we ask lots of auestions and do a lot of listening. This is a panel for industry  professionals-not for tne average fan attendee.

Title: Bug Hunt
Long Description: Bug Hunt Your ship is powerless after being struck by a meteor. You must navigate your way to the life pods, bypassing the ruptured compartments and avoiding predatory beasts. And, if that weren’t enough, you lost some of your gear in the impact, the ship’s down to emergency lighting, and the air is running out

Title: If I Ran TSR I Would...  (General Public)
Long Description: This is a panel that is designed to get feedback from our customers about what they like  and don't like about our products, and what they'd do differently if they were running  the show. Again we want to ask lots of auestions and listen to lots of responses. This  panel is open to all Gen Con attendees, but is going to be focused on products, not  channel issues.

Title: War in the Heavens Preliminary Battle
Tabula Rasa
Long Description: Tabula Rasa Immerse yourself in the mystery, intrigue, and terror of the new Alternity setting, Dark*Matter. Your heroes awaken in a padded room as “blank slates.” Now they must remember who they are, discover why they’ve been imprisoned, and find a wav out!

Title: AD&D Designing a Campaign, Part IV: The PC
Long Description: Designing a Campaign, Part TV: The Player Characters So, where do the player characters fit in? Are they dime-a-dozen adventurers or the heroes of the age? How world-shaking is their impact? A look at the final, and most important, part of the world-building puzzle.

Title: DUNGEON Adventures Playtest
Long Description: DUNGEON® Magazine Playtest	 Meet Dave Gross, editor of Dragon Magazine, and playtest an AD&D adventure scheduled for an upcoming issue!

Title: ALTERNITY Double Blind For AD&D Players
Long Description: AD&D/Altemity® Double Blind Two parties of adventurers—one from a high-fantasy AD&D setting, and the other from a high-tech Alternity universe—must race to uncover the secret nature of a powerful artifact. Is it a magical device left over from some legendary wizards’ war, or a powerful doomsday weapon built by a long-forgotten alien species?

Title: AD&D Forgotten Realms: Elminster Speaks!
Long Description: Elminster Speaks! Always entertaining and occasionally even honest, Elminster (Ed Greenwood) cuts up for the fans, abetted by designer Steven Schend (who ought to know better).

Title: Mindwalkers: Life Is But A Dream
Long Description: Mindwalkers: Life Is But a Dream The Psychic Wars are over. Play a group of desperate psionic freedom fighters as they try to elude search-and-destroy squads while striking one last blow for psionic independence! This scenario showcases as-yet-unreleased rules for new psionic skills and psychic combat.

Title: Once & Future Worlds
Long Description: Meet with TSR staff to reminisce about the Al-Qadim®, Birthright®, Dark Sun®, Gamma World®, Maztica®, Mystara®, Red Steel®, and Spelljammer® games. What made these worlds special to you? Which ones would you like to see return? We love all our lines, so convince us that you want them back and who knows what may happen!

Title: AD&D New Players for a  New Millennium
Long Description: Sometimes finding new players for your regular AD&D games can be a challenge! Join  us for a discussion of techniques, strategies, and advice tor locating, recruiting, and  teaching new players.

Title: Alternity A-Team Autographing
Long Description: Come meet some of the key players on the Altemity team. They'll be around to sign  anything you want signed, and Rich Baker will be there to sign his new Star*Drive novel.  Or if you want just to come by and say hello, that's fine too! See you there!

Title: Jagged Little Pill
Long Description: Alternity* Game Events jagged Little Pill Take a trip into the twisted mind of David Eckelberry, designer of the Stai ‘Drive® campaign setting! Mary Kezcus, famed holoactress, disa ipeared from her film studio a week ago. You’ve promised to bring her back... and earn a spot in the next movie.

Title: Pyramid Scheme
Long Description: Pyramid Scheme Be the first on your block to play in the brand-new Dark«Matter™ campaign setting! Search for the fabled lost knowledge of the Library of Alexandria through the darkest warrens of ancient Cairo and a hidden burial chamber in the shadow of the Pyramid at Giza.

Title: Alternity Welcome to Dark Matter
Long Description: Alternity House Rules What’s broken in the Alternity game? What did you do to tune the game to your own campaign? What should we do to fix it? Come to this seminar and tell us all about the house rules you use in your own game, and swap ideas with all the other Gamemasters present—including the TSR designers!

Title: Sixguns and Star Stalkers
Long Description: Six Guns and Star Stalkers Alte lity designer Richard Baker presents a scenario from his own camoaign. The year is 1885; the place is the windswept prairie of the Dakota Territory. Don’t let the screaming things in the night sky or the Gho in the Skin of a Man distract you!

Title: Saga System: Spell-O-Rama
Long Description: Spell-O-Rama! Come and take part in the third annual competition to determine the best three spellcasters on Krynn. Sorcery, mysticism, and prizes abound! Beginners welcome

Title: Altemity House Rules
Long Description: What's broken in the Altemity game? What did you do to tune the game to your own  campaign? What should we do to fix it? Come to this seminar and tell us all about the  house rules you use in your own game, and swap ideas with all the other gamemasters  present-including the TSR designers!

Title: Dragonlance: Children of Solace
Long Description: Children of Solace <(“ — The Red Dragon army has come to Solace, and they aren't here to admire the vallenwood trees. Can you save some local children from the depredations of this marauding horde? Pregenerated heroes will be provided for this untold tale of the War of the Lance.

Title: What's New at TSR
Long Description: Come visit the TSR staff and get the inside scoop on what's happening in the year 2000  and beyond!

Title: Merchandising Your Store
Long Description: This panel will discuss effective ways to merchandise game and book products in the  typical retail store. We'll talk about the economies of me business in a way that will be  accessible to the retailers-no corporate geekspeak. The focus is going to be on creating  effective product chains-sell the basic set, then the sourcebooks, then the adventures. A  discussion of how to interface with publishers to get support for this type of activity will  also be covered.

Title: AD&D The Best House Rules
Long Description: Every campaign is different, and every Dm has his or her own rules. Bring your home  rules to share and vote on the very best!

Title: AD&D Designing a  Campaign Part II: Villains
Long Description: What's a mountain climber with out a mountain? Come hear expert advice on choosing  the right villains to challenge your heroes.

Title: AD&D Forgotten Realms: Taking the Campaign Underwater
Long Description: As shown by Sea of Fallen Stars, Mel Odom's "Threat from the Sea" series, and the  upcoming The Wyrmskull Throne, Faerun is packed with opportunities for aquatic  adventures. Find out how to incorporate underwater activity into your Realms campaign.

Title: AD&D Forgotten Realms: Realms Round Table
Long Description: Famous-or notorious-Realms inhabitants discuss the state of Faerun and answer  questions.

Title: AD&D Forgotten Realms: All- Stars
Long Description: The realms All-Stars get together to swap stories, tell tall tales, and sign autographs

Title: AD&D Rant & Rave
Long Description: Need some R&R? We Do! Come tell us what you think-good and bad-about recent  AD&D products. Bring at least one "rant" ana one "rave." Then, talk to the people who  bring it to you.

Title: AD&D Designing a Campaign: Part 1: Gods
Long Description: So many gods; so little time. Advice from TSR designers and editors on creating the right  pantheon tor your game.

Title: AD&D Ravenloft: The Kargat  Files
Long Description: What terrible secret and horrible fates await heroes unlucky enough to enter the mists of  lavenloft? Join members of Kargat as we discuss recent comings and goings on the  Demiplane of Dread.

Title: AD&D Greyhawk: Welcome Back to the Flanaess
Long Description: You've run the Temple of Elemental Evil ten times for your campaign, each time different.  Join members of Team GREYHAWK in a round table discussion. Snare your secrets and  maybe even learn something from your fellow master DMs of Oerth.

Title: AD&D Greyhawk Round Table
Long Description: Find out what we have in store for the world of Greyhawk in the coming months. If you  have questions for the Greyhawk writers and editors, this the place to be!

Title: Gen Con for Retailers
Long Description: This panel will be a kick-off to the Gen Con event for retailers who want to maximize the  impact of the show on their stores. We'll present information on the other seminars and  events in this track. We'll talk about how to utilize the exhibit floor to good advantage.  We'll note things to look for. questions to ask players, and other ways to use the show as  a way to get a feeling for what's hot and what's not in the gaming industry.

Title: AD&D Dungeoncraft
Long Description: Meet the editors and columnists of Dragon Magazine to discuss the fine art of Dungeon Mastering, including creating your own campaign world and breathing life into it. Designing a Campaign, Part III: Social Setting Just how medieval do you want your fantasy? TSR designers and editors discuss realism versus playability and player expectations to help you find the right balance for your game.

Title: Gen Con for Distributors
Long Description: This panel will be a kick-off to the Gen Con event for distributors who want to maximize  the impact of the show on their distribution businesses. We'll present information on the  other seminars in this track. We'll talk about ways to meet effectively with the company  representatives from Wizards of the Coast, who's at the show, and what their job  functions are. We'll talk about the events we've scheduled that relates to getting  consumers interested at all levels to our products.

Title: AD&D All About DRAGON  Magazine and DUNGEON  ADVENTURES
Long Description: Learn what the editors of DRAGON Magazine and DUNGEON Adventures want to see  from contributors, find out what's in store for the coming year, and tell them you'd like to  see in the magazine.

Title: Slam-a-Thon Charity Benefit
Long Description: The biggest super hero battle of all time, and it's all for charity! Plus, everyone who  attends gets a free Toy Biz MARVEL action figure! Meet at the Marvel area of the  Wizards of the Coast booth in the exhibition nail.

Title: Who would win? You make the call?
Long Description: Spider-Man vs. the Hulk? Captain America vs. Iron Man? Who wins? Majority rules?  Place your bets, and then they'll throw down using the Marvel Super Heroes Adventure  Game!

Title: Dark Matter-Inter., The Big Lie
Long Description: Dark*Matter Interactive: The Big Lie Are you a bold truth-seeker, exposing hidden secrets for all to see? Or are you a conspirator, working to keep the unknown behind a veil of mystery? Every player’s got an identity, an agenda, and a secret to hide in this exciting Dark*Matter interactive event!

Title: The Ravenloft Drama
Long Description: The Eighth Annual Ravenloft Drama The TSR Players once again take to the stage with a classic tale of intrigue, horror, and bloody revenge. Perhaps this year we’ll get it right!

Title: Gen Con Gong Show
Long Description: Eveiyone thinks they have a great or hilarious gaming story-and some people actually  do! Bring your favorite story and share it at this traditional Gen Con event. Or. just come  to hear some entertaining tales and see those who don't entertain get gonged by our  panel of judges.

Title: STAR*DRIVE Author and Game Designer Reception
Long Description: This Reception is open to anyone who wants to know more about the Star’Drive novels,  authors, and game designers. Mingle with Diane Duane, Roland Green, Rich Baker, and  many more! Refreshments will be served. Remember to stop by the Wizards of the Coast  Author Autographing area first for your free invitation.

Title: Songs of the Saga
Long Description: A Gen Con Game Fair tradition! Come sing the songs that are famous throughout the  world of Krynn. New this year, the "Gnome Thinking Song” as well as the "Mt.  Nevermind Anthem"!

Title: AD&D Forgotten Realms: Author and Designer  Reception
Long Description: Come and meet your favorite authors and designers, including R.A. Salvatore, Ed  Greenwood, and many others. We'll have refreshments and conversation in a friendly  atmosphere. Remember to stop by the Wizards of the Coast autographing area first for  your free invitation.

Title: R. A. Salvatore Q&A
Long Description: Come meet R.A. Salvatore, author of The Cleric Quintet, The Dark Elf Trilogy and The  Silent Blade. Ask him about his future plans for your favorite FORGOTTEN REALMS  characters.

Title: Diane Duane Q&A
Long Description: Meet Dane Duane author of the Star'Drive novels Starrise at Corrivale and Storm at  Eldala, and ask her questions about her work.

Title: Author and Game Designer Reception
Long Description: Come and talk to your favorite authors up close and personal. Authors in attendance will  be Gen Con Game Fair Lifetime Guests of Honor Margaret Weis and Tracey Hickman as  well as Linda Baker, Steven Stan! Brown, Jeff Crook, Miranda Homer, Richard Knack,  Steve Miller, Douglas Niles, Chris Pierson, Jean Rabe, and many more! Refreshments will  be served. Remember to stop by the Wizards of the Coast Author autographing area  first for your free invitation.

Title: AD&D Dragonlance: Killer Breakfast
Long Description: Come and get a character splattered by the best in the business. Tracey Hickman, game  designer and co-author of the DragonLance Saga, hosts a hilarious, fast paced  roleplaying adventure. Keep your wits about you because if may be the only thing that  saves your characters life!

Title: Author, Artist and Designer Reception
Long Description: Come meet your favorite authors up close and personal. Guests include: Jeff Grubb, J.  Robert King, Vance Moore, Lynn Abbey, Loren Coleman, and Corey Herndon as well as  many of your favorite Magic: The Gathering artists and game designers. Refreshments  will be served. Remember to stop by the Wizards of the Coast Author Autographing  area first for your free invitation.

Title: Planescape: After The World Ends
Long Description: After the World Ends What if the third Millennium brought the Blood War to modern Earth? A live-action Mage/Planescape event; all rules and props provided on site. Details: <www.execpc.com/~mstan-ton/gencon>.

Title: Worlds of Spellfire  Seminar
Long Description: Join Mij Reltub, the Spellfire Oracle, as he discusses the latest and greatest about the  125 Spellfire card game. All members of the Design Team are invited to attend, so bring your  favorite Spellfire cards and have them signeaby your favorite Spellfire stars!

Title: Star'Drive Interactive: The Corner
Long Description: Star*Drive Interactive: The Corner “There’s nothing really like it... well, anywhere,” say the travel guides. And with that ambiguous recommendation, you are welcome to “The Corner”: part-watering hole, part-casino, and part-music lounge for heroes looking for a rest in the year 2502. Anything can happen here, and it usually does.

Title: Star*Drive Interactive: Blinded by the Light
AD&D TSR's 25th  Anniversary
Long Description: Meet the designers and editors of the TSR 25th Anniversary products. What's new?  What's the same? How do you like the originals? What do you think of the anniversary  editions.

Title: AD&D What's a DM to Do?
Long Description: TSR's Sage, Skip Williams, and a panel of veterans consider the toughest problems from  your roleplaying campaign. Bring a question for the panel or just sittack and enjoy the  show.

Title: AD&D Rant & Rave
Long Description: Need some R&R? We do! Come and tell us what you think - good and bad - about  recent AD&D products. Bring at least one "rant" and one "rave." Then, talk to the people  who bring it to you.

Title: AD&D Designing a  Campaign, Part III: Social  Setting
Long Description: Just how medieval do you want your fantasy? TSR's designers and editors discuss realisn  versus playability and player expectation to help you find the right balance for your  game.

Title: AD&D Forgotten Realms: You don't Know El!
Long Description: Think you know it all? Stump our illustrious panel of Realms savants with a non-rules  question and win a prize.

Title: AD&D Forgotten Realms: 1999 and Beyond
Long Description: What's coming up? Get glimpses into the future products, plans, and proposals for the  Realms.

Title: AD&D Planescape: At the Crossroads
Long Description: Scan the chant on what's up in the Planescape multiverse. You'll leave this seminar well-  tanned and ready to go planewalking.

Title: Worlds of Altemity
Long Description: What sets Star'Drive apart from Star Wars? What exactly makes Dark*Matter different  than The X-Files? Come join designers and editors for an introduction to the two  published settings for Altemity game, and a discussion of the possibilities for other  settings.

Title: Alternity Star*Drive Update:  The Verge of 2502
Long Description: Join members of the Star*Drive team as they talk about some of the events that have  affected the Verge in the last year and hint at those that may influence its future. This is a  very interactive session, so come ask your questions and share your thoughts with the  creative staff!

Title: What's New with  Alternity
Long Description: You've seen where the Alternity game has been - but where are we taking it next? let us  tell you. Better yet, you'll also get the inside scoop on where things will go next year, too!

Title: AD&D Saga System: A SAGA of Your Own
Long Description: TSR's quick, flexible SAGA Game Rules have garnered accolades for their use in classic  fantasy (DragonLance: FIFTH AGE Dramatic Adventure Game) and super-heroic  adventure (MARVEL SUPER HEROES Adventure Game) products. Come discuss how you  can apply this innovative, story-driven roleplaying game to any world - including your  own.

Title: Horror at TSR!
Long Description: Unseen powers, elder gods, deathless killers - there's more than one way to frighten a  PC! come chat with TSR designers and editors about what you think makes a great  horror game.

Title: The Good Old Days at TSR
Long Description: Join Kim Mohan, Harold Johnson, and other TSR stalwarts for a look back into TSR  history. The panel will recount triumphs, tragedies, and the joys of the TSR working  environment.

Title: Who's Who at Wizards of  the Coast
Long Description: This panel will focus on the brand, sales, and marketing teams. Well explain how the  organization functions, who's responsible for what, who to call for help, suggestions, or  to provide feedback. The intent of this panel is to demystify the sometimes Byzantine  structure of Wizards for both distributors and retailers.

Title: Alternity The Art of System  Building
Long Description: What's it take to put together a star system for your Altemity game? Veteran game  designers Bill Connors and Richard Baker take a look at the art - and science - of  creating playable and believable worlds for a science fiction game. It took four billion  years for the Earth to get where it is now; we'll cover the same ground in an hour!

Title: Marvel Super Heroes What's New at Marvel?
Long Description: You wanna know what's up at the World's Greatest Comics company and the new  roleplaying hit, the MARVEL Super Heroes Adventure Game? Come meet Mike Selinker,  designer of the Marvel game.

Title: Super Hero Round Table
Long Description: The top super hero game designers and developers go ahead-to-head in this free-for-all  discussion! A Gen Con classic!

Title: The Big Announcement
Long Description: TSR invites every Gen Con attendee to this very special forum. This is your chance to say  "I was there when ..."

Title: Publishers & Distributors:  How We Can Make the  Distribution Channel Work  Better
Long Description: This panel is designed to reveal how channel marketing and support programs are  supposed to function, and how to make the channel work more efficiently. We'll focus on  failures (like the TSR Gold Program) and successes (like the Clan Wars Banzai Kits). The  objective of this panel is for our distribution partners to learn how to access the services  we provide to the channel more effectively, and for them to help us understand the  unique challenges they have in implementing these programs.

Title: The Fun of Science Fiction Games
Long Description: Is the gaming scene still new to you (or to someone you're bringing to the show)? Well,  get thelxasics from Science Fiction Saturday. Our seminar "The Fun of Science Fiction  Game" covers the gamut form card games to board game to roleplaying games. We  know we can find the perfect game tor you!

Title: Cranberry Chicken
Long Description: Come share a late dinner with the RPGA. We have taken the slot off from most of our  gaming so you can enjoy the meal. The Living Death LARP players will be in costume  and sharing the Archaeological Society dinner while the rest of us share each other's  company, listen to guests entertain you with stories of the gaming industry, and help  honor those members who serve so hard during the year. The dinner will end by 10:30,  but the Living Death game will continue through the rest of the game slot. If you're not in  the game, you can go to the bar after dinner or get some sleep and be rested for the  Friday activities. Entree choices are: Cranberry chicken (event#l 661), roast pork (event  #3071), and baked vegetarian lasagna (event #3072).

Title: Ice Cream Social
Long Description: Ice Cream Social This special event is for Guild-level RPGA members and exhibitors only. Come have free ice cream and socialize with friends. We may even have a surprise or two planned. Free ice cream in the Labyrinth under the RPGA HQ in the Arena. . . as long as it lasts in the inferno of members who will come.

Title: Puffing Billy Ribbon
Long Description: Play unlimited Puffing Bill Games! Sponsor: TGA.

Title: Rubs of Warfare Year Three Qualifier
Live Action Kill Doctor Lucky
Long Description: Live-Action Kill Doctor Lucky Come on down to the J. Robert Lucky mansion, and do what gamers across the world have been doing for years: Kill Doctor Lucky. This amusing pre-mystery game pits players against one another in an all-out race to catch the old man alone, and kill him. It’s harder than it sounds: He’s not called "Doctor Lucky” for nothing. The live-action version is played on a huge map, and can accommodate as many as eight bloodthirsty killers.

LARP: The Good, The Bad and The Deadly
Long Description: The Good, The Bad, and The Deadly (Deadlands Live-Action) Location: The Safehouse, 779 Front Street. Last year the Explorers Society published a tell-all book: Rascals, Varmints, and Critters. It was suppressed by agents of the American government. Now the Explorers themselves are being eliminated. To expose the culprits, the society has announced a public reading of the material they don’t want you to know. All Explorers are invited. Rangers and Pinkertons are expected, and nobody knows who or what else might show up. Soon all will know who is the hunter and who is the hunted. Costumes welcome. Rules will be taught; all are invited. Entry fee includes lunch and drink ticket.

Title: Adventures of Capt. Proton: Nightmare in Paris!
Long Description: The Adventures of Captain Proton: Nightmare in Paris! Featuring a guest appearance by pulp author D.W. "Prof” Smith. The corridors of Voyager have taken on an eerie resemblance to the city of Paris-or are you just trapped in the holodeck? When holograms walk, and Captain Proton is nowhere to be found, it’s up to you to set things right! Be prepared to play a crewmember, a hologram, an alien, or any combination. Rules will be taught; all are invited.

Title: Council of Greyhawk Meeting
Long Description: Meet the people behind the Oerth Journal and the Greyhawk online following. There will  be mass revelry and open gaming following the meeting.

Title: RPG: Revenge in Mos Eisley
Long Description: Revenge in Mos Eisley Live-Action Adventures by West End; run by Fantasy Aspirations It is a dark time for all the galaxy. The struggle between the Galactic Empire and the Rebel Alliance has torn asunder all order and justice known in the fringe systems. Lawlessness grows like a hungry Star Dragon. Mos Eisley, already a wretched hive of scum and villainy, has degenerated into a state of syndicate warfare. In the wake of the death of the mighty Jabba the Hutt, many have come to Mos Eisley to seek fortune and power. But there looms an even greater threat from the very soul of Tatooine itself— which may spell the end for the wicked and noble alike.

Title: RPG: Time of Coming
Long Description: Time of Coming Live-action set in Legend of the Five Rings using modified L5R rules; run by Fantasy Aspirations A powerful daimyo’s only daughter is having her omiai ceremony. It is a chance for the powerful to make alliances, for the up and coming to advance in the world. Treachery, deceit, and romance will run rampant.

Title: RPG: Sleepy Pine Drama
Long Description: Sleepy Pine Drama Live-action set in the world of the soap opera; run by Fantasy Aspirations Sleepy Pine-the vacation spot of the wealthy, the hideaway of the stars. What happens behind closed doors is unbelievable .... Bring the melodrama, romance, and bad acting to the world of the soap!

The Creative Process: One  Writer's Approach
Long Description: Many people dream of becoming a writer, but what is it really like? How does the work  get done? Where do the ideas come from? what special problems are there? Award-  winning short story and novel Kij Johnson talks about her creative process and offers tips  from her experience.

Title: Beginning to Work:  Covering the Basis
Long Description: Regardless of genre, all writers use certain tools to create good fiction. Author Kij  Johnson discusses how to build plot and structure, characters, settings, dialogue, and  narrative-all the building blocks that work together to make a short story or novel  exciting.

Title: Critiquing Your Own Work
Long Description: Just because you've gotten the words down on paper doesn't mean your short story or novel is done. But what's next? In this session author Kij Johnson covers the stages of the rewriting process and how to critique and edit your own hction.

Title: Pinnacle Freelancer Meeting
Long Description: Pinnacle is always looking for fresh talent. Our Art Director will take the artists to a  separate meeting area to nand out our art guidelines and look at portfolios. Our editors  will also hand out guidelines, tell you what projects are coming up, and tell you  everything you need to know to write for one of our game lines.

Title: 7th Sea RPG GMs Seminar
Long Description: Run by John Wick and other design team members, learn how this remarkable world  came to be and how to use Theah to its fullest in your next 7th Sea campaign.

Title: Son of Stellar Screens
Long Description: Once again the Milwaukee Time Lords offer SF fans the latest news on the upcoming  television season and soon to be released movies. A question and answer session follow.

Title: Attack of the Killer Slush  (Pile)
Long Description: "It was a dark and stormy night..." Bulwer-Lytton look out! It's no secret that some  memorable manuscripts cross an editor's desk-but often they're ones the editor would  rather forget. Now our panel shares with you the best of the worst (all in good fun!)  Hopeful authors can expect to learn about the don'ts... and the don'ts of unsolicited  submissions.

Title: Pinnacle Jam Session
Long Description: Come and talk to the Pinnacle gang. We'll tell you what's coming up, what's going on,  and even hand out some nifty door prizes. After we have our way with you, you can  have your way with us. Ask us questions, make fun of our haircuts, find out about Brave  New World, and see if you can guess the answers to the remaining mysteries of  Deadlands.

Title: The Amazing Story
Long Description: When Hugo Gernsback founded this landmark science fiction magazine back with editor  and-chief Kim Mohan and the Amazing Stories editorial staff about the past, present,  and future of the world's first science fiction magazine.

Title: The Final Frontier Writer's  Workshop
Long Description: Now that you've learned the basics of writing science fiction, there's still a lot learn  about making your writing exceptional. In this free follow-up to her writer's workshop  series, Kij Johnson and her panel of authors discuss the nature of great science fiction  writing and offer suggestions, hints, and short-cuts you con apply to your own short  fiction or novels. Make your writing extraordinary.

Title: New World Order: One Big Deck Variants
X-Files: An Episode in an  Hour
Long Description: Brainstorm with Kevin J. Anderson, author of The X-Files novels Ground Zero, Ruins, and  Antibodies. For this hour, at least, YOU direct the conspiracy and engineer Mulder and  Scully's newest adventure. This story may never make it into an official episode guide,  but men again, who wants the "official" story anyway?

Title: Who's "Who" in Milwaukee
Long Description: Get together with the Milwaukee Time Lords, one of the area's premiere science of a  typical Milwaukee Time Lords meeting and expect a surprise or two along the way!

Title: Crossed Swords in Action!
Long Description: Back by popular demand, it's the Crossed Swords! Bat'leths fly as this dynamic husband  and wife stunt duo give live demonstration of how action-packed, staged-combaf fights  spice up your favorite sci-fi TV shows and movies. Their performances are filled with  behind-the-scenes gossip, tips on how to spot mistakes on screen, and lots of exciting  fight with new and different weapons.

Title: Warwick Davis Q&A and  Autographing
Long Description: What have you always wanted to know about the making of the Star Wars movies?  Now's your chance to get the inside info straight from Warwick Davis himself! Don't mis?  the opportunity to take a close-up look at a galaxy far, far away.

Title: Walter Koenig Press  Conference/Q&A
Long Description: Actor and author Walter Koenig, of Babylon 5 and Star Trek fame, takes questions from  the press and from fans. Spend some time with the talented actor who brought Psi Cop  Alfred Bester and Commander Pavel Chekov to life and find out all about his latest  projects.

Title: Babylon 5 Roundtable
Long Description: Too good to be true, you say? Not on Science Fiction Saturday! Join Babylon 5 actors  Julie Caidin Brown, Roblin Atkin Downes, and Walter Koenig, and author Neal Barrett,  Jr. as they reminisce about the roles they played in bringing to life the SF sensation that  was the last, best hope for mankind.

Title: CCG: Constructed Deck National Championship Qualifier
CCG: Constructed Deck National Championship Qualifier
CCG: Constructed Deck National Championship Qualifier
Warwick Davis  Autographing
Long Description: Warwick Davis meets fans and signs autographs in the Exhibit Hall's Autograph Area.  Get there early, as space is limited! This ticket does not guarantee you a space in line. It  is merely a reminder of the time and place.

Title: Babylon 5 Stars Autographing
Long Description: Two, two, two autographings in one! Babylon 5 fans can meet Julie Caiflin Brown, who  plays Na'toth, and Roblin Akin Downes, also known as Byron the rogue telepath, at the  Exhibit Hall's Autograph Area. Get there early for this session, as space is limited! This  ticket does not guarantee you a space in line. It is merely a reminder of the time and  place.

Title: If I Designed a Computer  Game
Long Description: Top-rate first-person shooter 3D graphics combined with artificial intelligence  roleplaying elements - in a full-body VR environment? Well, such a game may not exist  now, but we may not be as far from it as you think. Industry experts listen to your ideas  and share with you the secrets of the new technology that await us on the other side of  the millennium.

Title: Kevin J. Anderson Q&A
Long Description: Meet Gen Con Author Guest of Honor Kevin J. Anderson and learn about his rise to  New York Times bestseller status. Anderson offers tips to new writers and answers your  questions about his gaming background, Star Wars novel series, X-Files books, and all  his newest projects. This ticket does not guarantee you a space in line. It is merely a  reminder of the time and place.

Title: The Future of Star Trek
Long Description: With Deep Space Nine wrapping up. Voyager becomes the only first-run Trek show on  the air. Star Fleet Academy leads a discussion of what's on the horizon for our favorite  SF franchise. Where is Trek headed according to its producers? What would YOU like to  see happen next on Voyager? Don't miss your chance to sit in the captain's chair!

Title: Kevin J. Anderson  Autographing
Long Description: Bring your copies of Kevin J. Anderson's books to the Autograph Area in the Exhibit Hall  and have them personally signed by the author who hold the world's record for the  Igrgesf autographing in history! This ticket does not guarantee you a space in line. It is  merely a reminder of the time and place.

Title: Artist's Workshop
Long Description: Professional artist and industry lecturer Pamela Shanteau offers a free workshop for  future illustrators. Learn proven SF painting techniques, helpful shortcuts (such as using  projectors), and ideas for howto deal with problems of scale and other issues gemxme  to the SF artist. This free, hour long workshop also covers course material inmirations  and portfolio do's and don'ts.

Title: Star Wars Episode 1: If 1 Made the Movie
Long Description: Let's face it: When it comes to Star Wars, we're all wanna-be filmmakers. Join the  members of the U.S.S. Mudd-Pi to discuss how well this year's new film lived up to fans'  expectations and hopes. "Every generation has a legend," the trailer proclaimed. Did  this journey's first step live up to its legendary sequels?

Title: Ask Dr. Sciense-Live
Long Description: Amazing Stories proudly presents, live and on stage - the indomitable, inscrutable,  insufferable Dr. Sciense! The good doctor, along with his faithful friend Neal Barrett, Jr.,  steps out of the pages and into our faces to ponder questions that plague humankind  about "Sciense ana other stuff that's hard to understand." Don't miss Inis one-of-a-kind  answer man's hilarious premiere.

Title: Amazing Stories for Kids
Long Description: As part of the Game Fair's line of family programming this year's Science Fiction  Saturday is pleased to offer free SF storytelling each day at the Kid's Place, Gen Con's  own day care center. Bring your children ana while away an hour with one of our  entertaining guests as storyteller. You won't be disappointed-and you'll treasure the  special time with your kids. Or, take the opportunity to register your children (18months  o 1 Ojears) with The Kids Place for quality care at reasonable prices.

Title: Millennium Fever
Long Description: Feeling edgy lately? Looking over your shoulder a bit more than you used to? With the  approach of the year 2000, people find their minds drifting toward topics like UFOs,  government conspiracies, and even the end of the world. How does the coming of the  new millennium shape our collective thoughts and the media's messages? And where  does the truth lie amid the fever dreams?

Title: Star Trek Couch Potato
Long Description: Next time someone tells you to get out of your comfy chair and shut off the TV, tell him o  her to "please stand by"! Here's a time where if pays to be a couch potato! Star Fleet  Academy offers this Jeopardy style game show tnat features questions from your favorite  SF/F programs, such as Star Trek, Babylon 5, Hercules, and others to solve the puzzle.  Prizes will be awarded to trivia's top tubers.

Title: The Role of Books in Gaming
Long Description: Many of today's top SF authors were dice rollers long before they ever saw their name  on the cover of a book. Game designers and authors chat with you about their starts in  the business and the unique insights the roleplaying hobfw offers to them as writers.

Long Description: As part of the Game Fair's line of family programming this year's Science Fiction  Saturday is pleased to offer free SF storytelling each day at the Kid's Place, Gen Con's  own day care center. Title: Walter Koenig Autographing
Long Description: Walter Koenig, known in Star Trek circles as Mr. Chekov and to autographs at the  Precedence Booth in the Exhibit Hall, (see map elsewhere in this book for booth  location.) One free autograph per person; photos and books are available for sale at the  booth. No tickets required; first come first served. Participation is limited! This ticket does  not guarantee you a space in line. It is merely a reminder of the time and place.

Title: Writing Star Trek
Long Description: How do you capture in print the essence of James T. Kirk, Jean-Luc Picard, and other  Trek icons? How can you tell a good story without blowing up the Enterprise, starting  another galactic conflict, or permanently changing the lives of the bridge crew? Noted  author Diane Duane leads this panel of top-notch Star-Trek novelists in a discussion of  bringing the television classic to life on the printed page.

Title: Walter Koenig Autographing
Long Description: Walter Koenig, known in Star Trek circles as Mr. Chekov and to autographs at the  Precedence Booth in the Exhibit Hall, (see map elsewhere in this book for booth  location.) One free autograph per person; photos and books are available for sale at the  booth. No tickets required; first come first served. Participation is limited! This ticket does  not guarantee you a space in line It is merely a reminder of the time and place.

Title: Sci-Fi Auction Hour
Long Description: Babylon 5's Robiin Atkin Downes is the star auctioneer for our first-ever Science Fiction  Auction! Bid on everything from hard-to-find SF games and collectibles to autographed  memorabilia to special Gen Con-only items. Wouldn't that original celebrity portrait look  great on your wall? Ever wanted to have a character in a SF book named after you? All  mis and more awaits you. Proceeds from many items will be donated to charity.

Title: Son of Stellar Screens
Long Description: Once again the Milwaukee Time Lords offer SF fans the latest news on the upcoming  television season and soon-to-be released movies. A question answer session follows.

Title: Dinner with a Star: Julie Caitlin Brown
Long Description: Spend and evening among the stars! Dine personally with Babylon 5 actress Julie Caitlin  Brown! The first six people to register will receive dinner, an autograph, and pleasant  conversation with Na'loth herself at a fine restaurant Saturday evening near the  Convention Center, All proceeds go to charity, so seize this chance of a lifetime AND  help others at the same time!

Title: Star Wars: Future Fiction
Long Description: Dei Rey's authors and editors share with you the exciting new developments in the world  of Star Wars fiction, including the latest on the forthcoming book by R.A. Salvatore!  Don't miss this chance to hear the latest from those in the know and to tell them what  YOU want to see in their novel line.

Title: Dinner with a Star: Kevin J. Anderson
Long Description: Spend and evening among the stars! Dine personally with Game Fair's Author Guest of  honor Kevin J. Anderson! The first six people to register will receive dinner, an  autograph, and pleasant conversation. All proceeds go to charity, so seize this chance ol  a lifetime AND help others at the same time!

Title: Dinner with a Star: Warwick Davis
Long Description: Spend and evening among the stars! Dine personally with Game Fiction Guest of Honor,  Warwick Davis! The first six people to register will receive dinner, an autograph, and  pleasant conversation with this fabulous celebrity at a fine restaurant Saturday evening  near the convention center. All proceeds go to charity, so seize this chance of a lifetime  AND help others at the same time!

Title: Secrets of SF Game Design Workshop
Long Description: What makes a winning science fiction roleplaying scenario? How can you play out your  favorite Sci-Fi movies and TV shows-withouf your players ever getting wise? What does  it take to create a vibrant yet believable game setting? Learn the secrets behind all these  success strategies in our free daily game-design workshop, sponsored by the RFGA  Network.

Title: The Fun of Science Fiction
Long Description: Is the gaming scene still new to you (or to someone you're bringing to the show)? Well,  get the basics from Science Fiction Saturday. Our seminar "The Fun of Science Fiction  Game" covers the gamut form card games to board game to roleplaying games. We  know we can find the perfect game for you!

Title: Adventure Gaming: The  State of The Industry
Long Description: Join our distinguished panel drawn from the ranks of some of today's most successful  adventure gaming publishers, distributors, columnists and retailers to talk about the state  of the industry. The 90's have been a time of tremendous change and growth. This is  your chance to hear what the experts think about important trends in gaming, the  dominance of trading card games, the decline, fall, and rescue of TSR, the renaissance  of Games Workshop and tabletop miniature gaming, and the successes and failures of  game lines both large and small.

Title: AD&D/ALTERNITY Double Blind For Alternity Players
Long Description: Dark*Matter Interactive: The Big Lie Are you a bold truth-seeker, exposing hidden secrets for all to see? Or are you a conspirator, working to keep the unknown behind a veil of mystery? Every player’s got an identity, an agenda, and a secret to hide in this exciting Dark*Matter interactive event!

Title: A Star Wars State of Mind
Long Description: You're in it. You know it. That special state of mind grabbed you the minute you saw  your first Star Wars movie, ana it never really let go. Bill Slavicsek, author of The Guide  to the Star Wars Universe, chats with fellow authors Timothy Zahn, Kevin J. Anderson,  and Rebecca Moesta about the joys and ... Joys!... of our mutual condition.

Title: Futures Past and Present
Long Description: Yesterday the future looked like a ray guns and rocket ships. Today the future looks like  cyberware and FTL travel. What might the future look like tomorrow.

Title: 2nd Edition: Talk A Good Game VII
How to Market Your Work
Long Description: From paper based games to electronic games to novels and lots of places in between.  Artist Guest of Honor Keith Parkinson will lead a discussion on what it takes to market  your art so that it gets published.

Title: Keith Parkinson Q&A
Long Description: Get a chance to ask Keith Parkinson all those burning Questions.

Title: Keith Parkinson Slide Show
Long Description: Keith Parkinson shares past and perhaps current projects in this slide show.

Title: 2nd Edition: Alba Ker VII: In Too Deep
2nd Edition: Alba Ker VII: In Too Deep
Strategy and Tactics in  Modern Conflict
Long Description: Technology and tactics; how they relate and drive each other's development. This  seminar will discuss tactics and their evolution through the ages, as it relates to the  technology of the period. Topics covered will include: armor and the race to pierce it,  weapons and how they changed the tactics by their use, and the role of maneuver in  modern conflict. Presented by Stewart Davies, Dean of Tactics at the Strategic Defense  Institute.

Title: Timothy Zahn Autographing
Long Description: Best Selling Science Fiction author Timothy Zahn signs his work, including his Stars Wars  books (Heir to the Empire, Dark Force Rising, The Last Command, Specter of the Past,  and Visions of the Future) and other popular works. This will be held in the  Autographing are in the Exhibit Hall.

Title: Star Wars Autographing
Long Description: Star Wars authors from A (Kevin J. Anderson) to Z (Timothy Zahn) and more will be on con hand in the autograph area to sign books, photos, and almost anything else you might want to get a signature on. This will be held in the autographing area of the Exhibit Hall.

Title: LARP: Deep Space 1999: Survival Test
Long Description: Deep Space 1999: Survival Test” is an interactive game set on Star Trek’s Deep Space Nine station. As a Starfleet officer, Ferengi trader, Klingon warrior, or any of the other hundreds of characters available, you’ll interact with Captain Sisko and his officers in the Operations Center, pilot the Defiant, or even down a cold brew at Quark’s Bar. Your DS99 nametag gives you the role of a visitor to Deep Space Nine and introduces you to a labyrinthine plot of intrigue, mystery, and sci-fi excitement. DS99 runs continually Thursday through Sunday, but one event ticket lets you play whenever you want! Explore the Game Fair in search of others with DS99 nametags. Are your enemies searching for you, or might that stranger be a potential ally? You’ll never know unless you beam aboard.

Title: Penny for your Thoughts
Long Description: Babylon Project Interactive: The Gloves Come Off A Tale of Three Telepaths Babylon 5 fans, you’re in luck. No experienced LARPers allowed!

Title: Women in the Gaming  Industry
Long Description: Jean Rabe tells how women are becoming involved in the gaming industry. Hear how a  simple hobby can become a lifelong career. Jean tells how she progressed from a novice  player in college to becoming a freelance editor and game convention coordinator, to  RPGA Network coordinator, authoring novels and editing FASA's MECHFORCE  QUARTERLY. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Brainstorming
Long Description: Jean Rabe tells how to turn ideas from everyday life into an evening's game session or  compelling novel. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Writing for the Gaming  Industry
Long Description: Jean Rabe, editor of FASA's award winning MechForce Quarterly tells how to submit  games and fiction material to the Quarterly and other publications. Gen Con  Symposium.

Title: The Editor is Your Friend
Long Description: Margaret Weis tells how to work with editors and what you should expect from them anc  what they expect from you. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: First Get the Facts Straight
Long Description: Jean Black tells the writers what they need to know about writing non-fiction. Bring your problems and questions. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: You Can't Get There From  Here
Long Description: A look and the Endless Quest and other "Pick-a Path" books and how to write them. Gen  Con Symposium.

Title: Evolution of the Greyhawk World
Long Description: Gary Gygax, the master storyteller, explains how Greyhawk started and evolved into  such a mysterious and perilous location. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Not Really One of the Guys
Long Description: Liz Danforth provides a look at women and their contributions to the history of gaming,  including insights about the differences between male and female gaming styles, and the  gradual integration of women into the industry from 1975 to present. Gen Con  Symposium.

Title: Starving For Your Art
Long Description: Liz Danforth provides a look at the life of a freelance artist within the gaming industry. It  will include how and where to find work, a discussion of various techniques, and a  discussion of the gradual professionalization of the gaming industry and the graphic  presentation of products. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Secrets of a Best Selling  Author
Long Description: Mr. Stackpole is a New York Times best selling author. He tells how you can start on the  right foot as an author. He'll tell how he progressed as game designer to editor for  Flying Buffalo, to become one of the nations best selling SF and Fantasy writers. He  shares his tips and secrets and answers all your questions. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: War Against Gaming
Long Description: Mr. Stackpole frequently defends role-playing and gaming against assailants who claim  that gaming caused children to kill their parents, friends, etc. After telling of the exciting  cases he has worked on, he'll outline strategies for eliminating future threats to gaming  and avoiding persecution. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Gen Con Symposium Ribbon
Long Description: This ribbon allows you unlimited, free admission to all Gen Con Symposium Events.

Title: Gas, Bugs, and Nukes Part 1
Long Description: Major Wesely describes weapons of mass destruction, how they work, how they were  developed and how to simulate them in games. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: World War 2 Bombs and  Bombing Part 1
Long Description: Major Wesely describes the strategy, tactics and material used by each major power  trying to win victory through air power. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: American Civil War Firepower Part 1
Long Description: Major Wesely discusses the most important changes in weapons and tactics from the  Napoleonic wars to the Civil War. GENCON Symposium.

Title: Recent War Technology  Q&A
Long Description: Major Wesely tells about the newest weapons, their uses, etc. and answers questions  asked about his previous lectures. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Gas, Bugs, and Nukes Part 2
Long Description: Major Wesely continues his discussion of new weapons and unique ways they can be simulated in games. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: World War 2 Bombs and Bombings Part 2
Long Description: Major Wesely continues his discussion of Bomb Sights, the most effective aircraft, and  the Luftwaffe's master plan. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Civil War Firepower Part 2
Long Description: Major Wesely continues his revelations of advantages and disadvantages wrought by  the newest Civil War battlefield weapons. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Air Combat Game Designing  Secrets and Formulas
Long Description: Major Zocchi explains how to design authentically scaled air combat games for table top, board game format or computer adaptations Gen Con Symposium.

Title: How To Sell Your Game Design
Long Description: Major Zocchi tells everything you need to know to succeed in the game business. Copyrights, patents, trademarks, costs, royalties, pricing, profit margins, discounts, timing releases, agents, and getting someone else to publish your design, will be covered. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Battle of Britain Blunders
Long Description: Major Zocchi tells of major RAF and Luftwaffe blunders as well as errors made in his  Battle of Britain game design. Six exciting, new discoveries could have changed the  battle. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Boer War
Long Description: Mr. Maker explains why Great Britain was forced to field the largest expeditionary force  in its history, to fight a handful of farmers. He tells what made their guerilla warfare  tactics so effective and the long term consequences. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: French and Indian War
Long Description: Mr. Maker explains what happened from 1754 to 1760, as the British, French,  200 Colonists, Iroquois, and other Indian nations struggled for dominance and control over  North America. Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Boxer Rebellion
Long Description: Mr. Maker tells how and why the virulent, foreign hating Boxers, tried to control China.  Gen Con Symposium.

Title: Early Development of Roleplaying Games
Long Description: Early Development of Roleplaying Games-Robert Bledsaw shares how he developed his  Middle Earth role playing campaign and his group's assumptions regarding the correct  way to plav a role playing game. The evolution of campaign rules and coordinating the  activities of divergent players takes an unexpected turn. How he turned this campaign  into a series of products. The purpose of a roleplaying adventure gaming product is  defined. The philosophy of gaming is decided Dy consensus and modified by experience  Incorporating Dave Ameson's First Fantasy Campaign into the Judges Guild campaign  universe. Plans for bringing the Judges Guild universe into homes via the Internet and th  changes necessary to bring to do this.

Title: Developing an Ongoing Campaign
Long Description: Robert Bledsaw discusses general considerations when developing an on-going fantasy  roleplaying campaign. Magic and the elements of fantasy, which make each campaign  unique ana interesting, Defining the depth of play and setting the limits of expectations.  The preconceptions wnieh mustsbe identified and discussed with your group of players.  Pace and flow of the game in a randomly determined series of events such as cross-  country travel. The amount of effort put into adventures, which your players avoid,  shoula not be wasted,The advantages and disadvantages of computer assisted judging.  A brief and incomprehensive review of computer programs that help in the design  stages. Adjusting all the above to a science fiction role playinq campaiqn.

Title: Patching Together Your Own  Unique Game
Long Description: Robert Bledsaw shows how to combine rule sets and developing your own systems.  Realism in a role playing campaign and the disadvantages of being exact and correct.  Your efforts must match the expectations of your players. Judges mandate decisions  within the context of the rules and don't merely tell a story and manipulate rules to suit  the play or players. Judges like referees help the players enjoy the game by enforcing  the rules and suggesting changes to the rules to increase the enjoyment of the players.  Killer DMs miss me point and better than half the fun. Your score card: excitement,  enthusiasm, concern, and laughter. Group cohesion: the carrots and sticks necessary to  encourage group conflict resolution. When a player character dies. Science Opera or  Science Fiction depends on the group rational for playing the campaign. When worlds  collide: science fiction in fantasy roleplaying campaigns and vice versa. Moderator  Robert Bledsaw. (S-l)

Title: When Judges Pontificate
Long Description: Robert Bledsaw offers advice on introducing the new player to an established campaign.  Mysteries and puzzles beyond the capabilities of your group. Allowing players to make  errors in judgement and when to permit "fate to lake ahand". A role playing gamer or  a game playing actor? The problem player and his expectations. The judge is an  adversary. Permitting players to assume the role of an arch villain. When the  background requirements exceed your capability to keep up. The player killer or player  verses player when appropriate and inappropriate. The ultimate control of atmosphere  and appropriate behavior of player characters. Maturity and sex in role playing  campaigns. Notoriety and infamous ramifications. Revenge of the denizens. The  suspension of disbelief and involving the player in his role-playing persona. When  reality blurs. Back to the basics: when shock no long rocks. The short diversion or the  engrossing saga.

Title: Secrets of SF Game Design  Workshop
Long Description: What makes a winning science fiction roleplaying scenario? How can you play out your  favorite Sci-Fi movies and TV shows-withouf your players ever getting wise? What does  it take to create a vibrant yet believable game setting? Learn the secrets behind all these  success strategies in our free daily game-design workshop, sponsored by the RPGA  Network.

Title: Luke Peterschmidt & Ed Bolme Autographing
Long Description: Get your copy of the The DUELIST magazine (issues 22, 26, 30, 36, and 40) signed by  Luke Peterschmidt and Ed Bolme, game designers and brand managers for the Five  Rings Publishing Group. They also will be signing their trading card game work, so  bring your copies to the Periodicals section of the Wizards of the Coast booth in the  Exhibit Hall and meet the designers!

Title: Chris Metzen Starcraft  Autographing
Long Description: Get your copy of AMAZING Stories magazine signed by Starcraft game designer Chris  Metzen, whose story, "Revelations," in the Spring 1999 issue chronicles the first  encounter between human and Zerg. Chris will be signing his other work as well, so  bring your copies of Diablo, Starcraft, and Warcraft II to the Periodicals section of the  Wizards of the Coast booth in the Exhibit Hall and meet the author!

Title: Jeff Easley Autographing
Long Description: Get your copy of Dragon Magazine and Dungeon Adventures signed by artist Jeff  Easley, whose recent work graces the covers of Dragon issue 254 and 260 and  Dungeon issue 69. Jeff will be signing his other work as well, so bring your Easley  collection to the Periodicals section of the Wizards of the Coast booth in the Exhibit Hall  and meet the artist!

Title: What's Up with IFGS?
Long Description: Come find out what Live Action Roleplaying is all about with boffer and foam weapons.

Title: Roast Pork
Long Description: Come share a late dinner with the RPGA. We have taken the slot off from most of our  gaming so you can enjoy the meal. The Living Death LARP players will be in costume  and sharing the Archaeological Society dinner while the rest of us share each other's  company, listen to guests entertain you with stories of the gaming industry, and help  honor those members who serve so hard during the year. The dinner will end by 10:30,  but the Living Death game will continue through the rest of the game slot. If you're not in  the game, you can go to the bar after dinner or get some sleep and be rested for the  Friday activities. Entree choices are: Cranberry chicken (event#l 661), roast pork (event  #3071), and baked vegetarian lasagna (event #3072).

Title: CCG: Championship Advanced Tournament, TCG HQ
Chron X 1999 World  Championships
Long Description: Stop by Sony Online Entertainment (Booth # 847) on Saturday August 7th to catch the  Chron X World Championship Tournament live at Gen Con! The 32 winners of 1998-  1999 Professional Tournament Series have battled until only two remain. And they're  here at Gen Con, ready to go head to head for the chance to win $1,000 in hard cash,  a personalized one-of-a-kind virtual trading card and the title of Chron X World  Champion!
